Package com.poesys.db

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BatchException
    An exception that indicates that a batch processing command failed.
    Message
    Get the message from the PoesysDbBundle properties file or optionally from user-specified files.
    Properties
    Get the properties from the PoesysDbBundle properties file or optionally from user-specified files.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ConstraintViolationException
    An exception that indicates that a Data Transfer Object (DTO) violates a database or runtime constraint.
    DbErrorException
    A generic subsystem exception for the Poesys DB library that supports a list of arguments for error message processing, allowing an error processing client to construct an error message from a resource bundle by supplying any number of string arguments, and that supports rolling back the database transaction in the current tracking thread.
    DuplicateKeyNameException
    An exception that indicates that a primary key has duplicate column names.
    InvalidParametersException
    An exception that indicates that a parameterized method does not have a set of parameters that fulfills preconditions for the method.
    InvalidPrimaryKeyColumnException
    The column name supplied by the caller is an invalid column name for this primary key.
    NoPrimaryKeyException
    An exception that indicates that a data transfer object (DTO) does not contain a primary key suitable for performing an update or delete
    NoRequiredValueException
    An exception that indicates that a required value (a value that you must supply at runtime) is null
